FallenDevils.name: House of Devils
FallenDevils.description: The main Fallen faction that inhabit the Cosmodrome in Old Russia. Their faction color is red.

FallenExile.name: House of Exile
FallenExile.description: A faction of Fallen that were exiled from other factions that inhabit the Moon. Their faction color is green.

FallenKings.name: House of Kings
FallenKings.description: A secretive Fallen faction that inhabit the old space shuttle launch sites in the Cosmodrome in Old Russia. Their faction color is yellow.

FallenWinter.name: House of Winter
FallenWinter.description: The Fallen faction that inhabit the surface of Venus. Their faction color is turquoise.

FallenWolves.name: House of Wolves
FallenWolves.description: A ruthless Fallen faction that was once under the control of the Queen of the Reef. Their faction color is blue.

HiveHiddenSwarm.name: Hidden Swarm
HiveHiddenSwarm.description: The most common legion of the Hive. They wear red armor.

HiveSpawnOfCrota.name: Spawn of Crota
HiveSpawnOfCrota.description: A legion of Hive that serve Crota, Son of Oryx. They wear yellow armor.

HiveBloodOfOryx.name: Blood of Oryx
HiveBloodOfOryx.description: A legion of Hive that serve Oryx. They wear dark red armor with white markings.

HiveSilentBrood.name: Silent Brood
HiveSilentBrood.description: A Hive sect that serve Oryx from deep within the Dreadnaught's prisons. They wear turquoise armor.

HiveVenomOfOryx.name: Venom of Oryx
HiveVenomOfOryx.description: A rare Hive sect that are exclusive to The First Firewall mission.

VexHezenCorrective.name: Hezen Corrective
VexHezenCorrective.description: The main subtype of Vex found on the surface of Venus. They have bronze plating.

VexHezenProtective.name: Hezen Protective
VexHezenProtective.description: The second most common subtype of Vex that serve as protectors of key Vex structures. They have gold plating with white markings.

VexVirgo.name: Virgo Prohibition
VexVirgo.description: The main subtype of Vex found on the surface of Mars. They have silver plating.

VexAphix.name: Aphix Invasive
VexAphix.description: A rare subtype of Vex with notable spiky protrusions on their heads and have distinct red frames.

VexDivisive.name: Sol Divisive
VexDivisive.description: The subtype of Vex that protect the Black Garden. They are covered in overgrowth.

VexProgeny.name: Sol Progeny
VexProgeny.description: A collective of Ultra Minotaurs that protected the Black Heart and where designed to be its vessels.

VexPrecursors.name: Precursors
VexPrecursors.description: The subtype of Vex that existed in the past. They have white plating with gold trimmings.

VexDescendants.name: Descendants
VexDescendants.description: The subtype of Vex from the distant future. They have a more rounded design and look to be made from recycled materials.

Taken.name: Taken
Taken.description: Enemies that have been corrupted by Oryx's power that exist to serve his will.

FallenDevilSplicers.name: Devil Splicers
FallenDevilSplicers.description: A sub faction of the House of Devils that have augmented their bodies and weaponry with Siva.

IronLord.name: Iron Lord
IronLord.description: The remnants of the old Iron Lords, twisted and controlled by SIVA. Their names were Jolder, Felwinter and Gheleon.

Minor.name: Minor
Minor.description: A basic enemy with a red health bar. Certain enemies will come equipped with a shield.

Elite.name: Elite
Elite.description: A rare type of enemy with a red health bar found in certain Public Events and other places. Often shielded with damage resistance.

Major.name: Major
Major.description: A tougher enemy with a yellow health bar. Often more aggressive and will come equipped with heavier hitting weapons.

Ultra.name: Ultra
Ultra.description: A boss tier enemy. Significantly more health and tougher to take down.

DefensiveRoutine.name: Defensive Routine
DefensiveRoutine.description: When a Hobgoblin takes damage, they temporarily switch to a defensive routine that surrounds them in Solar energy and make them immune to incoming damage.

ServitorMelee.name: Servitor Melee
ServitorMelee.description: When in close proximity, it will release Ether pulses that drain enemy health.

UltraCaptainMelee.name: Melee
UltraCaptainMelee.description: Creates an area of effect shockwave when in close proximity.

KaliksEther.name: Ether Gorge
KaliksEther.description: After losing health, Kaliks will summon Archon Servants who will sacrifice themselves to replenish a portion of its health.

AnnihilatorTotem.name: Annihilator Totem
AnnihilatorTotem.description: During the bridge encounter, failing to keep a guardian under each totem while the center plate is active will trigger Crota's Annihilation ritual.

OracleDeath.name: Prophecy of Doom
OracleDeath.description: Guardians who fail to destroy Oracles will succumb to their prophecy and not only lose their light, but also die as well.

Detain.name: Detain
Detain.description: Surrounds targets inside a red barrier that halts movement and outgoing fire.

LostInTime.name: Lost in Time
LostInTime.description: If no one is left alive in the present, those that were sent through the timestream are lost in time and killed.

TimestreamTeleportation.name: Timestream Teleportation
TimestreamTeleportation.description: Atheon will randomaly teleport three guardians into the past or future.

TimesVengeance.name: Time's Vengeance
TimesVengeance.description: Successfully destroying the red oracles will trigger a buff that allows guardians to deal bonus damage to Atheon.

MedusasStare.name: Medusa's Stare
MedusasStare.description: Line of sight charged attack that deals damage based on the Gorgons from Vault of Glass.

AeonMaul.name: Aeon Maul
AeonMaul.description: Aggresive bursts of Void energy fired from two mounted turrets.

CyclopsBlast.name: Cyclops Blast
CyclopsBlast.description: Charged Void energy blasts that travel in a straight line and have a large explosion radius.

CyclopsTorchHammer.name: Torch Hammer
CyclopsTorchHammer.description: Lowering a Cyclops health 50% will trigger a discharge of Void energy fired in all directions.

QodronsGaze.name: Qodron's Gaze
QodronsGaze.description: Any Guardians who have not killed a Qodron's Eye will be trapped in a bubble that deals Temporal Shockwave damage.

GulrotBelch.name: Gulrot's Belch
GulrotBelch.description: A massive belch that covers guardians in bile and significantly reduces their movement speed for a short amount of time.

TakenShield.name: Ward of Darkness
TakenShield.description: Throws up a barrier that blocks incoming and outgoing attacks and heals a portion of its health.

TakenDarknessBolt.name: Darkness Bolt
TakenDarknessBolt.description: A wave of dark energy that screams forward in a straight line, blinding enemies in its path and dealing a small amount of Arc damage (registered in-game as Melee).

CorruptedLight.name: Corrupted Light
CorruptedLight.description: Continuously spawned by Keksis that if not channeled, will drain guardians of their light and suppress their abilities for a short period of time.

GraspOfTheKing.name: Grasp of the King
GraspOfTheKing.description: Oryx summons his Taken power to drain guardians of their light.

WillOfOryx.name: Will of Oryx
WillOfOryx.description: Oryx summons a blight distrubance on top of guardians that deals damage.

DarknessBlastMelee.name: Darkness Blast
DarknessBlastMelee.description: Oryx slams down his Willbreaker sword.

AcolytesEye.name: Acolyte's Eye
AcolytesEye.description: Fires an aggressive barrage of Void energy.

TakenMultiply.name: Multiply
TakenMultiply.description: Taken Psions will continuously multiply if not killed quickly.

TakenShieldBlast.name: Shield Blast
TakenShieldBlast.description: A charged burst of Arc energy the propels targets within a medium to close range.

TakenOracle.name: Taken Oracle
TakenOracle.description: These Oracles bathe Morphon in a green aura, making it immune to all attacks.

TakenDetain.name: Taken Detain
TakenDetain.description: Surrounds targets inside a green barrier that halts movement and outgoing fire.

ShieldKnights.name: Immunity Shield
ShieldKnights.description: Will not take damage unless nearby other Knight.

MultiShieldKnight.name: Layered Shield
MultiShieldKnight.description: Shield rotates through Arc, Solar and Void types.

ShieldOgre.name: Immunity Shield
ShieldOgre.description: Will not take damage unless Cursed Thralls are detonated in close proximity.

ShieldCenturion.name: Immunity Shield
ShieldCenturion.description: Will not take damage unless all other enemies have been killed first. Will also be stunned for a few seconds when their shield breaks.

WizardReturn.name: Wizard Summon
WizardReturn.description: Will summon back the other Wizards after a short period of time.

TeleportWizard.name: Teleport
TeleportWizard.description: Will continuously teleport around the arena.

BrotherShieldBlast.name: Shield Blast
BrotherShieldBlast.description: A ranged jetpack powered shield slam that knocks back target. When supercharged will leave a Sunspot at the point of impact.

BrotherMortarBlast.name: Mortar Blast
BrotherMortarBlast.description: A long range mortar attack that travels in an arc. The destination is marked with a blue target ring.

BrotherShield.name: Dome Shield
BrotherShield.description: During the second phase, Valus Tlu'urn will surround himself with a large dome shield that blocks incoming fire.

BalwurLostLight.name: Lost Light
BalwurLostLight.description: Killing Acolytes of Balwûr expands the radius of the Lost Light buff, which enables guardians to deal damage to Balwûr.

SaberWireRifle.name: Wire Rifle
SaberWireRifle.description: A mounted sniper rifle that deals Solar damage.

SaberTurret.name: Shank Turret
SaberTurret.description: Rapid-fire shank turrets that deal Void damage.

SaberDischarge.name: Discharge
SaberDischarge.description: A close range continual discharge of Arc energy, which also deals damage over time.

SiegeEngineArc.name: Environmental Hazard
SiegeEngineArc.description: The Siege Engine continually discharges Arc energy until it gets taken offline by Guardians.

SiegeEngineWreckingBall.name: Wrecking Ball
SiegeEngineWreckingBall.description: A large Golden Age wrecking ball crane that has been repurposed as a weapon on the left-hand side of the Siege Engine.

SiegeEngineDetonation.name: Siege Engine Detonation
SiegeEngineDetonation.description: If the replacement parts are not installed into the Siege Engine quick enough, it will result in its core overheating and exploding.

SivaSwarm.name: SIVA Swarm
SivaSwarm.description: A sphere of SIVA that slowly eats away at anything standing inside its range.

WretchedGaze.name: Wretched Gaze
WretchedGaze.description: The eye of an Ultra Ogre that has been crafted into a cannon that fires a stream of Void energy.

profiles.name: Phase One
profiles.description: In this phase, it has a mounted Wire Rifle that deals Solar damage.

profiles.name: Phase Two
profiles.description: In the second phase, it swaps out weapons with Shank Repeater Turrets that deal Void damage.

profiles.name: Phase Three
profiles.description: In the final phase, its core is exposed and continuously discharging Arc energy similar to the Warlock's Stormcaller super.

profiles.name: Phase Two
profiles.description: If Valus Mau'ual is killed first, Valus Mau'ual will gain a powerful slam attack to ward off enemies that get too close.

profiles.name: Phase Two
profiles.description: If Valus Tlu'urn is killed first, Valus Mau'ual will gain two homing rocket launchers on his back.
